ference on Speech Technology and Human-Computer Dialogue (SpeD),\n\nVol. , pp. 1–10.\n\nExternal Links: Document\n\nCited by: 2nd item.\n\n[22]\nO. Ronneberger, P. Fischer, and T. Brox (2015)\n\nU-net: convolutional networks for biomedical image segmentation.\n\nIn Medical Image Computing and Computer-Assisted Intervention – MICCAI 2015, N. Navab, J. Hornegger, W. M. Wells, and A. F. Frangi (Eds.),\n\nCham, pp. 234–241.\n\nExternal Links: ISBN 978-3-319-24574-4\n\nCited by: §II-A.\n\n[23]\nD. Salvi, V. Negroni, L. Bondi, P. Bestagini, and S. Tubaro (2025)\n\nFreeze and learn: continual learning with selective freezing for speech deepfake detection.\n\nIn 2025 IEEE International Conference on Acoustics, Speech and Signal Processing (ICASSP),\n\nVol. , pp. 1–5.\n\nExternal Links: Document\n\nCited by: §I,\n§II-C1,\n§IV-B,\nTABLE II,\nTABLE II,\nTABLE II,\nTABLE II,\nTABLE III,\nTABLE III,\nTABLE III,\nTABLE III,\nAcknowledgment.\n\n[24]\nB. Sun and K. Saenko (2016)\n\nDeep coral: correlation alignment for deep domain adaptation.\n\nIn Computer Vision – ECCV 2016 Workshops, G. Hua and H. Jégou (Eds.),\n\nCham, pp. 443–450.\n\nExternal Links: ISBN 978-3-319-49409-8\n\nCited by: §II-C3.\n\n[25]\nM. Tan and Q. Le (2019-09–15 Jun)\n\nEfficientNet: rethinking model scaling for convolutional neural networks.\n\nIn Proceedings of the 36th International Conference on Machine Learning, K. Chaudhuri and R. Salakhutdinov (Eds.),\n\nProceedings of Machine Learning Research, Vol. 97, pp. 6105–6114.\n\nExternal Links: Link\n\nCited by: §IV-A,\nTABLE I,\nTABLE I.\n\n[26]\nM. Todisco, X. Wang, V. Vestman, M. Sahidullah, H. Delgado, A. Nautsch, J. Yamagishi, N. Evans, T.H. Kinnunen, and K. A. Lee (2019)\n\nASVspoof 2019: future horizons in spoofed and fake audio detection.\n\nIn Interspeech 2019,\n\n pp. 1008–1012.\n\nExternal Links: Document,\nISSN 2958-1796\n\nCited by: 1st item.\n\n[27]\nC. Wang, J. Yi, X. Zhang, J. Tao, L. Xu, and R. Fu (2023)\n\nLow-rank adaptation method for wav2